  "notes": "Primary data taken verbatim from the RFEG official club page (7 rated recorridos: Negras M, Blancas M, Amarillas M, Azules F/M, Rojas F/M), each with per-hole Hdcp/Par/Metros and Vc/Vs. All internal checks pass: pars sum 35+36=71, stroke indexes are a permutation of 1-18 (RFEG uses the same allocation on every tee), each tee's 18 distances sum exactly to its published total. Golfshake independently corroborates totals converted to yards (6089yd~5566m Amarillas, 5492yd~5023m Azules, 5038yd~4610m Rojas), slopes 138/135/123/125 and the Azules men's rating 66.9. Discrepancy: an older club/marketing card reproduced on golfingholiday.com shows a different stroke-index allocation (SI 2 on hole 1, SI 1 on hole 11) and longer back-of-tee distances (championship tee 6552 m); the RFEG rated card used here is the current official handicapping card. Azules and Rojas are dual-rated; two entries emitted per tee with identical distances."
